cc:Agent.dc:title: Jakub Steiner, Cory Kontros, Oxygen icon team

flowRoot.flowPara: The python script will walk this SVG and search for layers that include the string 'plate'.
In each of this layer it looks for a text object with the label 'context'/'icon-name'. (the category in the "layer name" field)
It then iterates through all rect objects within that layer. It takes the dimensions of the rectangle and exports a bitmap to: /Breathe/#{width}x#{height}/#{context}/#{icon_name}.png
Make sure you edit your "path/icon name" to the layername and your plate and palette layers are hidden when saved.
